								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="222r" to="231v"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Teshuvot</title>
								<note>
									<p>Written in the same semi-cusive script as the marginal writing of the main portion of the manuscript.</p>
									<p>Concern the tractates Yevamot, Ketuvot, Ḳidushin, and Giṭin. Subscriptions refer to various authors, but mainly to <name type="person" role="author">Meir ben Baruch of Rothenburg</name> (b. 1215, d. 1293).</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="232r" to="233v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Discussions and decisions on the tractate Ḥulin</title>
								<note>
									<p>These two leaves were previously bound with Add. 17050, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">474</ref>.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
