					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment. </support>
								<extent>234 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>382</height>
										<width>265</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>300</height>
										<width>215</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>234 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 1 older and 2 modern paper flyleaves at the end). Folio 1 is a paper flyleaf. </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>28 complete quires: i-xvi8 (folios 2-209), separate folio 210, xxvii-xviii6 (folios 219-230), folios 231-234 (additions). </p>
									<p>Quires enumerated with Hebrew letters, cut away in the trimming. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Folios 1 and 9 largely illegible through damp.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="35" writtenLines="34">
									<p>Uniform layout. Visible quire by quire pricking and page by page (brown) plummet ruling, also for the margins. </p>
									<p>Commentary in a small semi-cursive script provided around the main text. </p>
									<p>Last line of writing written within the ruling. </p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable. </p>
									<p>Occasionally additional notes. </p>
									<p>Repeated words at the beginning of columns. </p>
									<p>Decorated horizontal catchwords. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Ashkenazi square and semi-cursive script of the 14th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Shemayah</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, folio 210v. Written for <name type="person" role="patron">Mosheh ben Yosef</name>: inscribed, folio 210. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus from="216r" to="221v"/>written in a different hand than the rest of the manuscript.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folios 232-233 were previously bound with another volume (Add. 17050). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person">Shemu᾿el de Modena</name>, dated <date calendar="Gregorian">1653</date>, <name type="place">Verona</name>: inscribed in a record of death: folio 234v. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Camillo Jaghel</name>: inscribed with his name, 1613 (folio 231v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">50-56</ref>. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Fra Giro[lamo] de Durazzano de Predi</name>[?]: censor's signature and note 1640 (folio 231v). (Narkiss reads the name Durallano), on him see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">89</ref>. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Laurentius Franguellus</name> (fl. until 1596): inscribed with his name, 1575 (folios 231v, 233v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">78</ref>, appendix § 105-110. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Renatus a Mutina</name>: insribed with his name, 1621 (folio 231v). </p>
						</additions>
